
Html attributes vs dom properties
____________________________________________


When writing HTML source code, you can define attributes on your HTML elements. Then, once the browser parses your code, a corresponding DOM node will be created. This node is an object, and therefore it has properties.

Attributes are defined by the html where as the properties by domain 

Attributes initialise Dom properties, once the initialisation is done, attribute job is done


Property value can change but attributes value can’t

________________________________


<input type="text" value="Name:">

has 2 attributes (type and value).


<input id="the-input" type="text" value="Name:">
the corresponding DOM node will have id,type, and value properties (among others):



You can access the html code by-



/*
document.getElementById('div1').addEventListener('click', () =>{
document.getElementById('div1').style.backgroundColor = 'red'
}
)
*/

const item = document.getElementById('div1')
item.style.color = 'red'
